WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.993
- Do you have therapy today?
- It's not therapy.

00:05.071 --> 00:07.403
- Well, you're seeing a psychiatrist.
- Not for therapy.

00:07.474 --> 00:09.567
- It's an official evaluation, okay?
- <i>[Siren Wails]</i>

00:09.642 --> 00:11.974
Person who found the body
is in the living room.

00:12.045 --> 00:14.070
Great. Crime scene first,
then we talk to the witnesses.

00:14.147 --> 00:16.081
- <i>Corpse is gonna be in the den.</i>
- Thanks.

00:16.149 --> 00:18.083
- What is that?
- What's what?

00:18.151 --> 00:20.210
- Your tie. It's staid.
- Staid?

00:20.286 --> 00:23.278
Yeah, and boring. It looks like
J. Edgar Hoover picked it out.

00:23.356 --> 00:26.450
- Look, it's something I'm workin' on, okay?
- In therapy?

00:26.526 --> 00:30.462
Gordon Gordon says that
the wild socks and the fancy ties...

00:30.530 --> 00:32.464
are all just, you know,
quiet rebellions...

00:32.531 --> 00:34.466
helping me suppress other impulses.

00:34.534 --> 00:36.468
- Isn't that good?
- You'd think so, right?

00:36.536 --> 00:39.733
But apparently, all the other issues
have to just rise to the top.

00:39.806 --> 00:42.297
Why do you call
your psychiatrist Gordon Gordon?

00:42.375 --> 00:45.139
'Cause that's how he introduces himself.
"Hi. I'm Gordon. Gordon Wyatt."

00:45.211 --> 00:47.975
Like "James. James Bond."

00:48.048 --> 00:50.346
"Bond. James Bond."

00:50.417 --> 00:53.750
Not "James. James"...James... Whatever.

00:53.820 --> 00:55.981
- <i>[Police Radio Chatter]</i>
- <i>[Saroyan] We're over here.</i>

00:56.056 --> 00:58.081
You might want to tuck
your pants into your socks.

00:58.158 --> 01:00.752
- <i>The flies get in everywhere.</i>
- [Groans]

01:00.827 --> 01:03.990
<i>What, no cartoon characters on the socks?</i>

01:04.063 --> 01:06.055
Never had cartoon characters
on the socks.

01:06.132 --> 01:08.692
They were just...
Uh... Never mind, okay?

01:08.768 --> 01:11.703
- What have we got here?
- Three weeks "decomp," give or take.

01:11.771 --> 01:13.762
- Oh. Place was tossed, huh?
- No forced entry.

01:13.840 --> 01:16.434
The victim is probably the man
of the house, Terrance Bancroft.

01:16.509 --> 01:19.535
<i>His wife Clarissa identified</i>
<i>the watch and wedding ring.</i>

01:19.612 --> 01:22.308
- This isn't good for me.
- Yeah, it's pretty gross.

01:22.382 --> 01:25.613
No, not that. There's too much
soft tissue for me to tell anything.

01:25.685 --> 01:29.519
- In fact, why am I here at all?
- The Bancroft family asked for us specifically.

01:29.589 --> 01:33.457
- They got some kind of pull?
- The Bancroft Wing at theJeffersonian.

01:33.526 --> 01:35.858
<i>Sixty million bucks</i>
<i>will buy a lot of good will.</i>

01:35.929 --> 01:39.558
- <i>Typical.</i>
- This dried crust here at the mouth...

01:39.632 --> 01:42.362
When the jugular's cut,
the air mixes with venous blood...

01:42.435 --> 01:44.528
and the negative pressure
causes an air embolism.

01:44.604 --> 01:47.801
- <i>Death is very quick.</i>
- So just sit there and stop complainin'.

01:47.874 --> 01:49.535
- <i>[Brennan] Bound.</i>
- <i>Multiple stab wounds.</i>

01:49.609 --> 01:51.543
<i>We need photos of these spatter patterns.</i>

01:51.611 --> 01:53.977
I bet this statue's worth
more than my house.

01:54.047 --> 01:57.574
You know, you should ask your therapist
about your issues with rich people.

01:57.650 --> 01:59.982
You're in therapy?

02:00.053 --> 02:03.147
- You've seen the socks.
- [Chuckles]

02:03.223 --> 02:05.714
<i>The victim's wife's in the kitchen.</i>

02:05.792 --> 02:09.091
I was... I was at the Vineyard for a month...

02:09.162 --> 02:13.826
and Terry was supposed
to be at his fishing camp in Idaho...

02:13.900 --> 02:15.834
<i>so the house was closed up.</i>

02:15.902 --> 02:18.234
And you didn't try to contact him
at all during that time?

02:20.006 --> 02:22.270
We spoke three weeks ago.

02:22.342 --> 02:26.278
Um, the day before
he was supposed to leave.

02:26.346 --> 02:29.110
<i>The cabin doesn't get cell service.</i>

02:32.018 --> 02:35.749
I heard the officers talking
about a possible home invasion.

02:35.822 --> 02:37.687
Definite possibility.

02:37.757 --> 02:40.055
Well, Terry supports
a youth center...

02:40.126 --> 02:42.117
on the other side
of the Anacostia River.

02:42.195 --> 02:44.060
Rough neighborhood. Tough kids.

02:44.130 --> 02:46.064
I was always afraid to go there...

02:46.132 --> 02:48.259
but he said it was because
I didn't really know them.

02:48.334 --> 02:51.633
Yeah. Listen, I'd like you to, uh, put a list...

02:51.704 --> 02:54.798
of things together
that might have gone missing...

02:54.874 --> 02:58.275
- and, uh, give me a call.
- Okay.

02:58.478 --> 03:00.378
[Beeping]

03:01.714 --> 03:03.807
- That the Bancroft case?
- Yeah.

03:03.883 --> 03:06.909
Looks like a home-invasion homicide, right?

03:06.986 --> 03:10.820
Yes. I'm running dental records now.
Cam is finishing up the autopsy.

03:10.890 --> 03:12.915
But Booth is pretty sure
it's Terry Bancroft?

03:12.992 --> 03:15.392
<i>Yes. There was a lot of insect activity.</i>

03:15.461 --> 03:17.395
Samples are at your work station.

03:17.463 --> 03:19.931
<i>Also the extension cord</i>
<i>used to tie him up...</i>

03:19.999 --> 03:22.092
<i>and everything that was</i>
<i>on top ofhis desk.</i>

03:22.168 --> 03:24.261
He was tied up?

03:24.337 --> 03:27.966
His heart was perforated, but there's
no blood in the thoracic cavity.

03:28.041 --> 03:29.975
He was stabbed after
he was already dead.

03:30.043 --> 03:32.341
What-What killed him?

03:32.412 --> 03:34.346
His jugular was punctured.

03:34.414 --> 03:36.905
Multiple stabs are congruent
with killers jacked on crystal meth...

03:36.983 --> 03:39.144
- or just plain adrenaline.
- Why kill him?

03:39.219 --> 03:42.347
No sign of forced entry.
He probably knew his attackers.

03:42.422 --> 03:45.016
- We have a match.
- <i>[Beeping]</i>

03:45.091 --> 03:48.322
<i>Confirmed. Terrance Bancroft.</i>

03:48.394 --> 03:50.487
He knew his killers?

03:50.563 --> 03:53.293
Are you all right?

03:53.366 --> 03:56.130
Yes. Yeah, absolutely.

03:57.971 --> 04:00.633
I'll-I'll get on insect analysis right away.

04:02.000 --> 04:08.074
